Noah Fant 8 Yd pass from Nathan Stanley (Miguel Recinos Kick)

videos.description: Hawkeyes' Jake Gervase gets an interception off the deflection and returns it 29 yards. The turnover leads to a field goal.
videos.headline: Iowa's Gervase gets INT on tip-drill

videos.description: The Eagles' AJ Dillon plunges in from 4 yards out to give BC a 7-3 lead over Iowa in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Boston College's Dillon powers in for TD

videos.description: Nathan Stanley finds Noah Fant for an 8-yard touchdown to give the Hawkeyes a 10-7 lead over BC in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Iowa reclaims lead with 8-yard TD pass

videos.description: Tommy Sweeney catches a 39-yard touchdown pass from Darius Wade off the deflection to give the Eagles a 14-10 lead in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Boston College executes tip-drill to perfection for TD

videos.description: AJ Dillon rushes for a 66-yard gain for the Eagles that leads to an Eagles field goal to extend the lead.
videos.headline: BC's Dillon rumbles for a big gain

videos.description: The Hawkeyes' Akrum Wadley scores from 5 yards out to tie the game 17-17 in the third quarter.
videos.headline: Iowa's Wadley ties game with short TD

videos.description: Darius Wade hits Tommy Sweeney on the screen for a 48-yard gain to put the Eagles in the red zone.
videos.headline: BC's Wade, Sweeney connect for big gain

videos.description: The Hawkeyes' Anthony Nelson sacks BC's Darius Wade for a sack and strips him for force fumble. Parker Hesse recovers the fumble for Iowa.
videos.headline: Iowa's Nelson comes up big with strip sack

videos.description: The Hawkeyes' Drake Kulick powers in for short touchdown to give Iowa a lead again over BC in the fourth quarter.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Iowa's Kulick muscles in for go-ahead TD) 2017/12/27

videos.headline: Iowa's Kulick muscles in for go-ahead TD

videos.description: The Hawkeyes' Joshua Jackson get his FBS leading eighth interception of the season to stop the BC drive.
videos.headline: Jackson seals Hawkeyes' win with INT

videos.description: Behind 258 all-purpose yards from Alkum Wadley, the Hawkeyes' defeat Boston College 27-20.
videos.headline: Hawkeyes are New Era Pinstripe Bowl champions
